The paper proposes a method for improving multi-agent online planning in stochastic domains by approximating a value function based on emergent system behavior using reinforcement learning. This involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and reinforcement learning (cs.LG). The application domain is a smart factory environment, which involves robotics and automation (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
